<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/672: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chief of the American Representation on the Preparatory
                                Commission</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-20T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                        1928—noon</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. With reference to your 10, March 19, 7 p.m., your conclusion that it
                            would be most desirable to abstain as far as possible from participation
                            in debate on the Russian proposals is heartily endorsed. The proposals
                            are not of primary interest to this Government and we should not assume
                            a leading role in the discussions under any circumstances.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>